Yesterday we lost 13 United States Service Members:

11 Marines 
1 Navy Men 
1 Army Soldier 

Sons. Brothers. Fathers. Friends.

This is what we know so far of the young men that lost their lives. I urge you to join me in prayer for the families as they cope with the unimaginable heartbreak from yesterday’s events. (When we are given the remaining four names I will share them.)

It should’ve NEVER come to this! 

As I find out more information on how to donate and support these families I will share it with you all. 

We MUST get our Citizens and Troops OUT!
